    <h1>How to Enter the Tournament</h1>
    
    <p>
        To participate on the first Intergalactic Tournament you will need to create an account at <a href="http://www.orionsbelt.eu">orionsbelt.eu</a>.
        Once you've done that you'll need to make a payment and then go to the War Zone and register on the tournament. You'll will
        be placed on the tournament's player list until the tournament starts.
    </p>
    
    <h1>How to Prepare for the Tournament!</h1>
    
    <p>
        The Orion's Belt combat system is very fun to play, but you'll need to know it well to be able to face the best players. You need to know
        the <a href="http://manual.orionsbelt.eu/en/UnitIndex.aspx">combat units</a> and its abilities, and you'll need to know how a game is played. 
        The first thing you must do is to get to know the basic <a href="http://manual.orionsbelt.eu/en/Battles/BattleConcepts.aspx">Battle Concepts</a>.
        When you start the first battle you'll have a live tutorial that will teach you how to move your units on the user interface. 
    </p>
    
    <p>    
        To practice, the best way is to enter the game <a href="http://s1.orionsbelt.eu/Campaigns/Default.aspx">Campaigns</a>, where
        you'll face our AI bots. The bots aren't very smart but they'll help you to understand the game. There are several levels you must play
        that will introduce you to the combat units and the game's mechanics.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        There are also several known  tactics that you should know in order to be the best on the board. You can find them at the manual under
        <a href="http://manual.orionsbelt.eu/en/Battles/BattleTactics.aspx">Battle Tactics</a>. 
        On the <a href="http://gazette.orionsbelt.eu/">Gazette</a>, you have available several
        <a href="http://gazette.orionsbelt.eu/category/battle-analysis/">commented battles for analysis</a>.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        When you get to know the game, you can enter our <a href="http://s1.orionsbelt.eu/Tournaments.aspx">Mini Tournaments</a>.  
        These are tournaments that are started as soon as they get
        16 participants. These mini tournaments are free, and anyone can play on them. They are a great way to test your skills against
        other players.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        Last but not least, you can always <a href="http://s1.orionsbelt.eu/Battle/CreateFriendly.aspx">start a friendly match</a> with other players 
        to test specific tactics or combat units. Orion's Belt
        has a great community and you'll have lots of players that will gladly skirmish against you.
    </p>
    
    <h1>About Orion's Belt</h1>
    
    <p>
        The Orion's Belt <a href="http://www.orionsbelt.eu">browser game</a> is a free online 
        <a href="http://gazette.orionsbelt.eu/free-online-strategy-turn-based-game/">turn based strategy game</a> that you play on a browser
        against other players around the world. 
        You don't need any downloads to play this <a href="http://gazette.orionsbelt.eu/sci-fi-free-mmorpg-multiplayer-browser-game-orions-belt/">sci-fi game</a>. 
        The battles on this <a href="http://blog.orionsbelt.eu/?p=489">tactical mmo</a> are placed on a <a href="http://gazette.orionsbelt.eu/space-sci-fi-chess-game/">sci-fi chess variant</a>, 
        where you have powerful combat units at your disposal to face your opponent.
    </p>
    
